```

In server `Program.cs`, after `var app = builder.Build();`, add seed data initialization:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
    await SeedData.InitializeAsync(db);
}
```

Note: Since we're adding `await` at the top level, make sure the app.Run() is also `await app.RunAsync();` and the code uses top-level async.

### Step 13: Build and verify

Run `dotnet build` from the solution directory to verify everything compiles.

### Important implementation notes:
- Do NOT add `@rendermode` to any page — global Auto is already set in App.razor.
- The tracking page (`/track/{TrackingNumber}`) uses `.AllowAnonymous()` on the API so customers don't need to log in.
- The dispatcher pages (`/shipments`, `/shipments/new`, `/shipments/edit/{Id}`) require authorization.
- Make sure to create the `Models` and `Services` directories in the `.Client` project.
- Make sure to create the `Services` directory in the server project.

